---
import '../styles/global.css';

const siteName = "Clean Plate AI";
const siteUrl = "https://cleanplateai.com";
const contactEmail = "support@cleanplate.app";
const lastUpdated = "March 3, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — {siteName}</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Clean Plate AI — how we collect, use, and protect your data." />
</head>
<body class="bg-white">

  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="border-b border-border">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-5 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-primary-dark font-semibold text-lg no-underline">
        ← Back to Clean Plate AI
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Content -->
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-main mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-text-light text-sm mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Pnt Studio ("we," "our," or "us") operates the {siteName} mobile application. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong class="text-text-main">Account Information:</strong> When you create an account, we collect your email address and an encrypted password via Firebase Authentication.</p>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong class="text-text-main">User Preferences:</strong> Dietary restrictions, health goals, and ingredients you choose to avoid. These are stored to personalize your experience.</p>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong class="text-text-main">Scan Data:</strong> Photos you take of restaurant menus are processed for text extraction and analysis. Menu text and analysis results are stored in your account.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-text-main">Subscription Information:</strong> Subscription status is managed by RevenueCat and the respective app store (Apple App Store or Google Play). We do not directly collect or store payment information.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>To provide and improve menu analysis and health scoring</li>
          <li>To personalize results based on your dietary preferences and health goals</li>
          <li>To maintain your scan history</li>
          <li>To manage your subscription</li>
          <li>To communicate important updates about the service</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">We use the following third-party services to operate the app:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-text-main">Firebase (Google):</strong> Authentication and database storage</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-main">Google Cloud Vision API:</strong> Optical character recognition (OCR) to extract text from menu photos</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-main">Anthropic Claude API:</strong> AI-powered health analysis of menu items</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-main">USDA FoodData Central API:</strong> Verified nutrition data lookup</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-main">RevenueCat:</strong> Subscription and purchase management</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">Each service processes data according to their own privacy policies. We only share the minimum data necessary for each service to function.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is stored securely in Google Firebase (Firestore). We use security rules to ensure that only you can access your own data. All network communications use HTTPS encryption.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your account data, preferences, and scan history for as long as your account is active. When you delete your account, all associated data is permanently removed from our systems.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">7. Account Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          You can delete your account at any time from within the app (Preferences → Delete Account). This permanently removes your account, all scan history, preferences, and associated data. Account deletion does not cancel active subscriptions — manage subscriptions through your device's app store settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">8. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for advertising or marketing purposes. Data is only shared with the third-party services listed above as necessary to provide the app's functionality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our app is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us so we can remove it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">10. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-2">
          <li>Access your personal data (viewable in-app)</li>
          <li>Delete your account and all associated data (in-app)</li>
          <li>Update your preferences at any time (in-app)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes through the app or via email. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main mb-3">12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, contact us at
          <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`} class="text-primary-dark underline">{contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="border-t border-border mt-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-6 text-center text-text-light text-sm">
      © 2026 Pnt Studio. All rights reserved.
    </div>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
